            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I've been running into the same issue (I want to make `n` do different things depending on whether the register is empty or not). What I have noticed is that `let @/ = \"\"` (or the equivalent Lua `vim.fn.setreg(\"/\", \"\")` actually does clear the register --- it's just that `n` puts it back in for some reason.",
